---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Professional Experience | AJ Gamble"
	description="Proven track record in operational leadership and process optimization."
	heroImage="/aj-gamble-headshot.jpg"
>
	<h1>Proven Operational Track Record</h1>
	<p>
		I believe that operational excellence is not a state of being, but a continuous process of refinement. Below are specific case studies demonstrating how I have navigated operational chaos and delivered measurable results.
	</p>

	<section class="case">
		<h2>Operational Case Study: McKissick Products</h2>
		<div class="case-grid">
			<div>
				<h3>The Challenge</h3>
				<p class="muted">Fragmented communication between production planning and shop floor personnel led to unrealistic scheduling, low morale, and poor accountability.</p>
			</div>
			<div>
				<h3>The Strategic Intervention</h3>
				<p class="muted">Implemented <strong>radical transparency</strong> by posting real-time performance metrics in the shop. Established a daily cross-functional synchronization meeting to negotiate capacity and balance workloads.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="result">
			<h3>The Bottom Line Result</h3>
			<p class="big">On-Time Delivery Performance increased from <span class="from">55%</span> to <span class="to">95%</span>.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="case alt">
		<h2>Strategic Scaling: The Crosby Group</h2>
		<div class="case-grid">
			<div>
				<h3>The Challenge</h3>
				<p class="muted">The organization lacked visibility into the full manufacturing lifecycle—from raw material to final shipment—creating a disconnect between Sales promises and Production realities.</p>
			</div>
			<div>
				<h3>The Strategic Intervention</h3>
				<p class="muted">I bridged the gap by acting as an operational translator, leveraging my shop-floor experience to dismantle silos. I implemented a robust KPI framework including OTIF (On-Time In-Full) shipments, quote turnaround, and region-specific growth tracking.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="result">
			<h3>The Bottom Line Result</h3>
			<p class="big">Scaled annual revenue from <span class="from">$31M</span> to <span class="to">$82M</span> within 4 years.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="case">
		<h2>Operational Excellence: Industrial Splicing</h2>
		<div class="case-grid">
			<div>
				<h3>The Challenge</h3>
				<p class="muted">Managed internal sales and production coordination in a high-pressure rigging shop environment characterized by siloed communication and strained relations between office and floor staff.</p>
			</div>
			<div>
				<h3>The Strategic Intervention</h3>
				<p class="muted">Transformed workflow by establishing two-way communication channels with production management, balancing customer delivery promises with shop capacity, and maintaining a "hands-on" presence on the floor to foster mutual respect.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="result">
			<h3>The Bottom Line Result</h3>
			<p class="big">Achieved <span class="to">$1.2M</span> in annual sales (2025)—outperforming the next highest agent by over 30%—and secured high-level trust with key industrial accounts like Zeeco through consistent, reliable data accuracy.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="timeline-section">
		<h2>Career Timeline</h2>
		<ul class="timeline">
			<li>
				<strong>Inside Sales Associate II</strong> &mdash; Industrial Splicing and Sling LLC <span class="muted">(2024&ndash;2026)</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>CNC Machine Operator</strong> &mdash; Wood Systems <span class="muted">(2023&ndash;2024)</span>
				<p class="muted">Set up and operated CNC machinery to manufacture precision components, interpreting production tickets and technical documentation to ensure exact dimensional accuracy.</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>CNC Machine Operator</strong> &mdash; Southern Millwork, Inc. <span class="muted">(2017&ndash;2023)</span>
				<p class="muted">Operated precision horizontal mills to exacting industrial specifications, building a hands-on foundation in manufacturing processes and quality control that continues to inform how I approach operations leadership today.</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Manager of International Operations and Inside Sales</strong> &mdash; The Crosby Group <span class="muted">(2011&ndash;2015)</span>
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Production Planner</strong> &mdash; McKissick Products (The Crosby Group) <span class="muted">(2007&ndash;2011)</span>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="case alt">
		<h2>What Colleagues Say</h2>
		<div class="quote-grid">
			<blockquote>
				"A.J. is an assertive, dedicated, task-oriented individual who would be an asset to any professional team, group, or organization. He is very self-motivated by his pride and his desire to be part of a successful project. I have worked with A.J. on multiple corporate-level project teams, and I am very impressed by his strong contributions."
				<footer>&mdash; Darin Herndon, Operations Manager at MP Innovations LLC</footer>
			</blockquote>
			<blockquote>
				"A.J. is a very detail-oriented person who works to streamline processes for maximum efficiency... A.J. is not a 'band-aid' type of person, he fixes the problem. He is a hard charger that would be extremely valuable to any organization that needs to bring order to chaos, or is looking to increase customer satisfaction and sales. I would highly recommend him for a senior position in any company!"
				<footer>&mdash; Steve Smith, Global Sales &amp; Growth Executive</footer>
			</blockquote>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style>
	.case {
		margin: 4rem 0;
		padding: 3rem;
		background: var(--bg2);
		border: 1px solid var(--line);
		border-radius: 8px;
	}
	.case.alt {
		background: transparent;
	}
	.case h2 {
		font-size: 2rem;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}
	.case-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 3rem;
	}
	.case h3 {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		font-family: 'Archivo', sans-serif;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}
	.muted {
		color: var(--soft);
	}
	.result {
		margin-top: 2rem;
		padding-top: 2rem;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
	}
	.big {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		font-weight: bold;
	}
	.from {
		color: var(--soft);
	}
	.to {
		color: var(--brass);
	}
	.timeline-section {
		margin: 4rem 0;
	}
	.timeline-section h2 {
		font-size: 2rem;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}
	.timeline {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		border-left: 2px solid var(--line);
		margin-left: 0.5rem;
	}
	.timeline li {
		padding: 0 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
		position: relative;
	}
	.timeline li:last-child {
		padding-bottom: 0;
	}
	.timeline p {
		margin: 0.25rem 0 0;
	}
	.quote-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 2rem;
	}
	blockquote {
		margin: 0;
		font-style: italic;
		color: var(--paper);
	}
	blockquote footer {
		margin-top: 1rem;
		font-style: normal;
		font-weight: bold;
		color: var(--soft);
	}
	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.case {
			padding: 1.5rem;
		}
		.case-grid,
		.quote-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: 2rem;
		}
	}
</style>
